node.title: Altercation in Velodrome car park before man died of injuries  - police
node.description: Victim died on New Year's Day
node.content:
["Police say an altercation took place between two groups in the Velodrome car park before a man later died in hospital. ", "In a statement police said they are continuing the investigation into the death of the 21-year-old man, who died shortly after being taken to Middlemore Hospital at 6am on New Year's Day 
", ""Police enquiries have established that there has been an altercation between two groups of people in the Velodrome carpark in Manukau early yesterday morning.
", ""Police carried out a scene examination at the Velodrome yesterday and this is now complete."", "The victim has been identified but won't be named until all of his family have been notified of his death. 
", "Police said they are working with the family and assure the community they are following a number of lines of inquiry. 
", "The homicide investigation was launched on Saturday morning after the victim died of his injuries in Middlemore Hospital. 
", "Anyone with information regarding the incident at the velodrome between the hours of 5am and 6am is asked to contact Police on 105 quoting file number 220101/8975.
", " "]
